WEBVTT

00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:03.779
Welcome to JW Broadcasting.

00:00:03.779 --> 00:00:07.780
In this month's program, we'll see how Jehovah shepherds us

00:00:07.780 --> 00:00:09.779
through any challenge.

00:00:09.779 --> 00:00:12.779
Here are some highlights of what's ahead.

00:00:12.779 --> 00:00:15.779
In the exciting conclusion to Luda's story,

00:00:15.779 --> 00:00:20.780
she must overcome her fears to make a stand for God's Kingdom.

00:00:20.780 --> 00:00:23.780
Where can we find the strength to make needed changes?

00:00:23.780 --> 00:00:28.780
A highly trained soldier tells us why he decided to leave the military

00:00:28.780 --> 00:00:31.780
after learning the truth.

00:00:31.780 --> 00:00:36.780
And our music video reminds us that joy and peace are possible now

00:00:36.780 --> 00:00:39.780
as we wait for the real life to come.

00:00:39.780 --> 00:00:43.780
This is the May 2024 edition of JW Broadcasting.

00:00:43.780 --> 00:01:05.700
What do you see when you look at this picture?

00:01:05.700 --> 00:01:08.700
Do you see yourself in it?

00:01:08.700 --> 00:01:11.700
You should, but why?

00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:15.700
This picture helps us to visualize the beautiful description

00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:19.700
of Jehovah, founded Isaiah 40, verse 11.

00:01:19.700 --> 00:01:23.700
Like a shepherd, he will care for his flock.

00:01:23.700 --> 00:01:26.700
With his arm, he will gather to gather the lambs.

00:01:26.700 --> 00:01:30.700
And in his bosom, he will carry them.

00:01:30.700 --> 00:01:33.700
He will gently lead those nursing their young.

00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:36.700
Jehovah bears many titles in the Bible,

00:01:36.700 --> 00:01:41.700
but the designation shepherd is among the most tender.

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:47.700
Like a shepherd, Jehovah says he will carry his lambs in his bosom,

00:01:47.700 --> 00:01:53.700
illustrating his tender love and care for each one of his precious sheep.

00:01:53.700 --> 00:01:56.700
Look again at the picture.

00:01:56.700 --> 00:02:02.700
Is it hard for you to see yourself as a lamb nestled in the bosom of our shepherd Jehovah?

00:02:02.700 --> 00:02:05.700
We know that many of you dear brothers and sisters are coping

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:09.699
with very difficult challenges day after day

00:02:09.699 --> 00:02:12.699
in this cruel wicked world.

00:02:12.699 --> 00:02:15.699
Such challenges can make it difficult for you to feel

00:02:15.699 --> 00:02:20.699
like a lamb safe and secure in the bosom of our shepherd.

00:02:20.699 --> 00:02:24.699
Please be assured that Jehovah is fully aware

00:02:24.699 --> 00:02:27.699
of every challenge you face.

00:02:27.699 --> 00:02:30.699
Why can you be so sure?

00:02:30.699 --> 00:02:35.699
Let's read what David, the writer of Psalm 23, verse 4 says,

00:02:35.699 --> 00:02:38.699
Though I walk in the valley of deep shadow,

00:02:38.699 --> 00:02:40.699
I fear no harm.

00:02:40.699 --> 00:02:47.699
For you are with me, your rod and your staff reassure me.

00:02:47.699 --> 00:02:53.699
Much like a physical valley located deep in the shadows of nearby mountains,

00:02:53.699 --> 00:02:58.699
a figurative valley can be used to describe a low point in one's life

00:02:58.699 --> 00:03:03.699
when we're feeling down, gloomy, or in a dark place.

00:03:03.699 --> 00:03:10.699
When David wrote this Psalm, he was feeling down at a low point in his life.

00:03:10.699 --> 00:03:14.699
Well, what valley of deep shadow are you currently going through?

00:03:14.699 --> 00:03:19.699
Are you feeling overwhelmed with trying to provide for your family's needs?

00:03:19.699 --> 00:03:24.699
Dealing with a serious health issue such as cancer?

00:03:24.699 --> 00:03:30.699
Exhausted because you're caring for your mate or a parent with dementia?

00:03:30.699 --> 00:03:33.699
Trying to cope with the death of a loved one?

00:03:33.699 --> 00:03:39.699
Baddling feelings of loneliness, worthlessness, or anxiety?

00:03:39.699 --> 00:03:42.699
Or facing persecution?

00:03:42.699 --> 00:03:49.699
It's so difficult to remain positive when facing the darkest days of our life.

00:03:49.699 --> 00:03:51.699
But there's a bright side.

00:03:51.699 --> 00:03:53.699
What is that?

00:03:53.699 --> 00:03:58.699
Jehovah is aware of the mountain-like obstacles that cause you to feel low

00:03:58.699 --> 00:04:01.699
as if you were in a valley of deep shadow.

00:04:01.699 --> 00:04:06.699
He not only sees your pain, but he's ready to come to your rescue,

00:04:06.699 --> 00:04:13.699
lift you up with his strong arms and embrace you like that lamb in the picture.

00:04:13.699 --> 00:04:18.699
Psalm 23 is one of the most well-known passages in the Bible

00:04:18.699 --> 00:04:25.699
and beautifully describes the loving way that our shepherd Jehovah leads, protects,

00:04:25.699 --> 00:04:28.699
and feeds his precious sheep.

00:04:28.699 --> 00:04:32.699
As we consider these three ways that Jehovah cares for us,

00:04:32.699 --> 00:04:36.699
look for the answers to the following questions.

00:04:36.699 --> 00:04:38.699
What does Jehovah do?

00:04:38.699 --> 00:04:40.699
How does he do it?

00:04:40.699 --> 00:04:43.699
And what do you need to do?

00:04:43.699 --> 00:04:45.699
The first way.

00:04:45.699 --> 00:04:48.699
Our shepherd leads us.

00:04:48.699 --> 00:04:52.699
At Psalm 231, the theme of our discussion,

00:04:52.699 --> 00:04:55.699
David expressed with full confidence,

00:04:55.699 --> 00:04:57.699
Jehovah is my shepherd.

00:04:57.699 --> 00:04:59.699
I will lack nothing.

00:04:59.699 --> 00:05:03.699
As a young man, David proved to be a capable shepherd

00:05:03.699 --> 00:05:07.699
who tenderly cared for and protected his entire flock

00:05:07.699 --> 00:05:12.699
and cared for the specific needs of each sheep.

00:05:12.699 --> 00:05:17.699
Here in Psalm 23, David portrays himself not as a shepherd,

00:05:17.699 --> 00:05:22.699
but as a humble sheep under the loving care of Jehovah,

00:05:22.699 --> 00:05:26.699
affectionately calling him my shepherd.

00:05:26.699 --> 00:05:31.699
During his lifetime, David experienced many highs and lows,

00:05:31.699 --> 00:05:36.699
peaks, valleys, joys, and disappointments.

00:05:36.699 --> 00:05:40.699
But whatever value of deep shadow he faced,

00:05:40.699 --> 00:05:44.699
David always relied on his shepherd to lead him to safety

00:05:44.699 --> 00:05:50.699
and provide exactly what he needed when he needed it.

00:05:50.699 --> 00:05:53.699
With complete trust and confidence, he said,

00:05:53.699 --> 00:05:56.699
I will lack nothing.

00:05:56.699 --> 00:06:02.699
No wonder Psalm 23 has been called a psalm of assurance or trust.

00:06:02.699 --> 00:06:06.069
What does our shepherd do?

00:06:06.069 --> 00:06:09.069
Verses 2 and 3 answer.

00:06:09.069 --> 00:06:12.069
In grassy pastures, he makes me lie down.

00:06:12.069 --> 00:06:16.069
He leads me to well-watered resting places.

00:06:16.069 --> 00:06:18.069
He refreshes me.

00:06:18.069 --> 00:06:23.069
He leads me in the paths of righteousness for the sake of his name.

00:06:23.069 --> 00:06:27.069
The watchtower once explained, David here paints a scene of

00:06:27.069 --> 00:06:32.069
contentment, refreshment, and security.

00:06:32.069 --> 00:06:37.069
Jehovah leads us to grassy pastures and tranquil waters.

00:06:37.069 --> 00:06:41.069
The Hebrew word rendered pastures can mean pleasant place.

00:06:42.069 --> 00:06:45.069
If we humbly follow our shepherd,

00:06:45.069 --> 00:06:49.069
he will lead us to a pleasant place where we can feel secure

00:06:49.069 --> 00:06:55.069
and have peace of mind, even when we're going through a valley of deep shadow.

00:06:55.069 --> 00:06:58.069
How does Jehovah lead us?

00:06:58.069 --> 00:07:02.069
By means of his word, he teaches us how to make wise decisions

00:07:02.069 --> 00:07:05.069
that lead to paths of righteousness,

00:07:05.069 --> 00:07:10.069
a life course that is pleasing to him and brings us happiness.

00:07:11.069 --> 00:07:15.069
He sets a course and a pace that we're able to follow,

00:07:15.069 --> 00:07:19.069
never expecting us to do more than we're able.

00:07:19.069 --> 00:07:24.069
Jehovah also leads us by means of undershepherds, the elders,

00:07:24.069 --> 00:07:29.069
who tenderly care for us spiritually, emotionally, and physically,

00:07:29.069 --> 00:07:33.069
so that we will lack nothing.

00:07:33.069 --> 00:07:35.069
What do you need to do?

00:07:35.069 --> 00:07:38.069
If you're going through a valley of deep shadow,

00:07:38.069 --> 00:07:43.069
search our many publications for specific Bible principles

00:07:43.069 --> 00:07:47.069
and helpful advice that can shed light on your present circumstances

00:07:47.069 --> 00:07:51.069
and provide practical ways to overcome difficulties

00:07:51.069 --> 00:07:55.069
or give you the patience to endure.

00:07:55.069 --> 00:08:00.069
Many find encouragement and comfort watching JW Broadcasting.

00:08:00.069 --> 00:08:03.069
In fact, one sister said,

00:08:03.069 --> 00:08:07.069
JW Broadcasting has helped me to be more positive.

00:08:07.069 --> 00:08:10.069
When I get lonely or discouraged,

00:08:10.069 --> 00:08:15.379
I find an encouraging talk or a morning worship program to watch.

00:08:15.379 --> 00:08:21.379
Are you benefiting from the monthly broadcasts, videos, and uplifting songs?

00:08:21.379 --> 00:08:26.379
The second way, our shepherd protects us.

00:08:26.379 --> 00:08:30.379
Let's read the second half of verse four.

00:08:30.379 --> 00:08:34.379
Your rod and your staff reassure me.

00:08:34.379 --> 00:08:39.379
David used a shepherd's rod and staff to illustrate Jehovah's protective care.

00:08:39.379 --> 00:08:43.379
Ancient shepherds used a rod to protect their sheep from predators,

00:08:43.379 --> 00:08:48.379
such as lions, bears, wolves, and snakes.

00:08:48.379 --> 00:08:54.379
They also used a staff to guide their sheep, gently nudging them in the right direction.

00:08:54.379 --> 00:08:59.379
Interestingly, some staffs had a hook at the end of the long stick

00:08:59.379 --> 00:09:06.379
that helped them as a shepherd gently draw back a sheep, strain, or nibbling into danger,

00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:10.379
guiding them back to the protection of the flock.

00:09:10.379 --> 00:09:16.379
The sheep certainly did not fear that the shepherd would use his rod or staff to beat them.

00:09:16.379 --> 00:09:19.379
What does Jehovah do?

00:09:19.379 --> 00:09:24.379
Our loving shepherd stands ready to use his figure of rod and staff to warn

00:09:24.379 --> 00:09:28.379
and protect us from predators seeking to harm us,

00:09:28.379 --> 00:09:36.379
especially from Satan, who in the Bible is portrayed as a vicious lion and a cunning serpent.

00:09:36.379 --> 00:09:43.379
Jehovah also has appointed elders in the congregation to warn and protect us from harmful influences

00:09:43.379 --> 00:09:48.379
and from taking a dangerous path in this wicked world.

00:09:48.379 --> 00:09:53.379
No doubt, you're filled with heartfelt appreciation and are comforted knowing

00:09:53.379 --> 00:10:01.379
that Jehovah is always on the lookout to use his figure of rod and staff to warn and protect us,

00:10:01.379 --> 00:10:03.379
not to beat us.

00:10:03.379 --> 00:10:08.379
If you strayed or nibbled away from the flock for whatever reason,

00:10:08.379 --> 00:10:16.379
please listen to Jehovah as he speaks to you through his written word, the Bible, and our brotherhood.

00:10:16.379 --> 00:10:22.379
Humbly follow the gentle nudging to lead you back to the safety of the congregation,

00:10:22.379 --> 00:10:30.379
where you'll enjoy lush, grassy pastures and refreshing well-watered resting places.

00:10:30.379 --> 00:10:39.379
Elders, you are entrusted with a privilege, but a heavy responsibility to protect Jehovah's precious sheep,

00:10:39.379 --> 00:10:42.379
whom he's placed under your care.

00:10:42.379 --> 00:10:50.379
We take this opportunity to express our sincere appreciation for those of you who use your figure of rod and staff

00:10:50.379 --> 00:10:59.379
to protect the sheep, never making them feel beaten down, but truly loved and appreciated.

00:10:59.379 --> 00:11:02.379
How does Jehovah protect us?

00:11:02.379 --> 00:11:06.379
He protects us as a group or flock.

00:11:06.379 --> 00:11:11.379
Satan will never succeed in wiping Jehovah's sheep from the earth.

00:11:11.379 --> 00:11:15.379
Jehovah also protects each sheep individually.

00:11:15.379 --> 00:11:17.379
How?

00:11:17.379 --> 00:11:21.379
Most important, he protects us spiritually.

00:11:21.379 --> 00:11:24.379
The draw close to Jehovah book explains,

00:11:24.379 --> 00:11:31.379
our loving God protects us from spiritual harm by equipping us with what we need in order to endure trials

00:11:31.379 --> 00:11:34.379
and to safeguard our relationship with him.

00:11:34.379 --> 00:11:42.379
Jehovah thus works to preserve our life, not just for a few short years, but for eternity.

00:11:43.379 --> 00:11:53.379
How reassuring that Jehovah makes sure that we have everything we need so that we will in effect lack nothing?

00:11:53.379 --> 00:11:56.379
What do you need to do?

00:11:56.379 --> 00:12:02.379
Take full advantage of the many provisions Jehovah makes available to protect us spiritually.

00:12:02.379 --> 00:12:09.379
Prayer, fellow worshippers, and timely spiritual food, which we'll discuss next.

00:12:10.379 --> 00:12:11.379
The third way.

00:12:11.379 --> 00:12:14.379
Our shepherd feeds us.

00:12:14.379 --> 00:12:18.379
Psalm 23 verses 5 and 6 reassures us,

00:12:18.379 --> 00:12:22.379
you prepare a table for me before my enemies.

00:12:22.379 --> 00:12:24.379
You refresh my head with oil.

00:12:24.379 --> 00:12:27.379
My cup is well filled.

00:12:27.379 --> 00:12:32.379
Surely goodness and loyal love will pursue me all the days of my life,

00:12:32.379 --> 00:12:36.379
and I will dwell in the house of Jehovah for all my days.

00:12:36.379 --> 00:12:38.379
What does Jehovah do?

00:12:38.379 --> 00:12:42.379
David now describes our shepherd as a generous host,

00:12:42.379 --> 00:12:50.379
who spreads before us his invited guests delicious and nutritious food and drink in great abundance.

00:12:50.379 --> 00:12:53.379
How does Jehovah feed us?

00:12:53.379 --> 00:12:58.379
Through the Faithland Discrete Slave, Jehovah gives us timely publications,

00:12:58.379 --> 00:13:04.379
as well as rich spiritual programs at our meetings, assemblies, conventions,

00:13:04.379 --> 00:13:08.379
JW broadcasting, governing body updates,

00:13:08.379 --> 00:13:13.379
along with encouraging songs and videos, and so much more.

00:13:13.379 --> 00:13:17.379
Truly, the slave is giving us food at the proper time,

00:13:17.379 --> 00:13:20.379
what we need when we need it.

00:13:20.379 --> 00:13:24.379
We certainly lack nothing spiritually.

00:13:24.379 --> 00:13:27.379
What do you need to do?

00:13:27.379 --> 00:13:32.379
Show your appreciation for the food the slave provides by eating it

00:13:32.379 --> 00:13:37.379
and never being fussy, picky, or selective in your eating habits.

00:13:37.379 --> 00:13:43.379
Remember, the Bible and Bible-based publications are ways that Jehovah speaks to us

00:13:43.379 --> 00:13:48.379
in effect saying, this is the way, walk in it, my precious sheep.

00:13:48.379 --> 00:13:53.379
As we read the Bible and meditate on the verses that touch our heart,

00:13:53.379 --> 00:13:58.379
we'll be better equipped to correct any faulty thinking that could lead us

00:13:58.379 --> 00:14:07.379
to dark feelings of anxiety, loneliness, worthlessness, anger, or resentment.

00:14:07.379 --> 00:14:13.379
Like David, be determined to dwell in the house of Jehovah for all your days.

00:14:13.379 --> 00:14:18.379
Continue attending our upbuilding meetings, assemblies, and conventions

00:14:18.379 --> 00:14:23.379
where we receive spiritual nourishment and protection.

00:14:23.379 --> 00:14:27.379
A sister who has traversed various valleys of deep shadow

00:14:27.379 --> 00:14:32.379
expressed what helps her to stay focused and keep on enduring.

00:14:32.379 --> 00:14:34.379
She said,

00:14:34.379 --> 00:14:36.379
depressive thoughts are not trustworthy.

00:14:36.379 --> 00:14:42.379
They are the product of a treacherous heart that distorts our thinking abilities.

00:14:42.379 --> 00:14:48.379
But because I trust Jehovah completely, each Bible verse proves to be

00:14:48.379 --> 00:14:56.379
like a solid stepping stone that enables me to gradually climb out of my many valleys of deep shadow.

00:14:56.379 --> 00:15:02.379
Our sister expressed so well how we feel about our loving shepherd

00:15:02.379 --> 00:15:09.379
who promises to help us successfully navigate through any valley of deep shadow.

00:15:09.379 --> 00:15:13.379
Isn't this a beautiful picture of a shepherd with his sheep?

00:15:13.379 --> 00:15:18.379
It's a door in the governing body conference room since the 1970s.

00:15:18.379 --> 00:15:23.379
It's a visual reminder of the importance of their work as shepherds.

