shepherds protect the sheep, but then shepherds also care for injured or ailing sheep.

00:16:32.379 --> 00:16:36.379
But the fact is that all of God's people are sheep.

00:16:36.379 --> 00:16:44.379
And so we have the privilege to follow the lead of Jehovah and Jesus and the elders

00:16:44.379 --> 00:16:49.379
and work together in unity. At the governing body meeting,

00:16:49.379 --> 00:17:00.379
we sometimes look at the picture and we try to apply what is implied in the painting

00:17:00.379 --> 00:17:05.380
to our work with the congregations and the worldwide flock.

00:17:05.380 --> 00:17:09.380
Thank you, brother Loach, for sharing those encouraging comments with us.

00:17:09.380 --> 00:17:15.380
How reassuring it is to know that our loving shepherds on the governing body

00:17:15.380 --> 00:17:21.380
take their responsibility to lead, protect, and feed you, me,

00:17:21.380 --> 00:17:24.380
and all of Jehovah's precious sheep very seriously.

00:17:24.380 --> 00:17:29.380
May we all continue to humbly and obediently follow their lead

00:17:29.380 --> 00:17:33.380
as we follow closely the lead of our great shepherd Jehovah

00:17:33.380 --> 00:17:38.380
and in the footsteps of our fine shepherd and King Jesus.

00:17:38.380 --> 00:17:45.380
Never forget that Jehovah is not just our shepherd, he is your shepherd,

00:17:45.380 --> 00:17:52.380
he is my shepherd, with Jehovah our shepherd leading, protecting, and feeding us.

00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:58.380
We can face a future with complete confidence and echo the words that David used to introduce

00:17:58.380 --> 00:18:03.380
this beautiful and reassuring psalm, the words contained at Psalm 23.

00:18:03.380 --> 00:18:08.380
Jehovah is my shepherd, I will lack nothing.

00:18:08.380 --> 00:18:14.789
One of the many valleys of deep shadow that we can pass through is war.

00:18:14.789 --> 00:18:20.789
Along with physical and emotional strain, it can threaten our loyalty to God's kingdom.

00:18:21.789 --> 00:18:26.789
How can we overcome fear and stand with Jehovah?

00:18:26.789 --> 00:18:30.789
The following dramatization takes us into the heart of a conflict

00:18:30.789 --> 00:18:35.789
and is based on the real life experiences of some of our brothers and sisters.

00:18:35.789 --> 00:18:43.789
Though I walk in the valley of deep shadow, I fear no harm for you are with me.

00:18:43.789 --> 00:19:19.890
Those words felt new when the fighting started again.

00:19:19.890 --> 00:19:23.890
But the family that took us in was a gift from Jehovah,

00:19:23.890 --> 00:19:37.240
while we waited for the trains to start running again.

00:19:37.240 --> 00:19:39.240
We tried our best to help others.

00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:48.259
They're nearly finished, I'm going to go help them clean up.

00:19:48.259 --> 00:19:58.859
Luda.

00:19:58.859 --> 00:20:00.859
Yaki.

00:20:00.859 --> 00:20:03.859
I know her from school.

00:20:03.859 --> 00:20:10.640
This is my brother Pablo, he protects this whole area.

00:20:10.640 --> 00:20:13.640
I'm surprised you're still here.

00:20:13.640 --> 00:20:15.640
You too.

00:20:15.640 --> 00:20:18.640
Why? I stayed to help the fight.

00:20:18.640 --> 00:20:20.640
Where else would I be?

00:20:20.640 --> 00:20:22.640
Oh, no, I just meant...

00:20:22.640 --> 00:20:23.640
This is our home.

00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:28.269
Everybody has to do their part to support the war.

00:20:28.269 --> 00:20:32.339
I'm...

00:20:32.339 --> 00:20:42.089
You're what?

00:20:42.089 --> 00:20:44.089
Jesus Jehovah.

00:20:44.089 --> 00:20:46.089
They don't care about the country.

00:20:46.089 --> 00:20:49.089
Oh, the cowards.

00:20:49.089 --> 00:21:03.069
Your people should be shot.

00:21:03.069 --> 00:21:08.329
Let's go.

00:21:08.329 --> 00:21:09.329
I just froze.

00:21:09.329 --> 00:21:14.559
Fear is natural.

